translated: Eckerström, Sten Gustav Emil, chief physician, Gothenburg, b. February 23rd, 1903 in Stockholm to Major Gustaf Peterson and Ida Eckerström. Married on July 31st to gymnasium director Harriet Minten. Children: Harriette-Marianne b. 1933, Claes-Göran b. 1936, Ulf b. 1938, Gunnar b. 1942. Completed high school in Gothenburg in 1921, earned a bachelor's degree in medicine in Stockholm in 1924 and a medical degree in 1929. Studied in Copenhagen, Oslo and London from 1936-1938. Worked as an assistant physician and temporary resident doctor at the pediatric ward of Gothenburg's hospital in 1928-1929, on a naval medical scholarship from 1929-1930, as a second-grade naval physician in Malmö in 1930, and as a first-grade naval physician in 1940. Worked as an assistant physician in the medical department of Sahlgr. hospital in 1929-1930, as an understudy physician at Gothenburg's city sanitation center at Kålltorp from 1930-1931, in the medical department of Jönköping's hospital from 1931-1932, as an assistant doctor in the medical department of Sahlgr. hospital from 1932-1934, as an understudy physician there in 1934, and as an assistant physician in the epidemic hospital in Gothenburg from 1938-1939. Was an understudy physician in the clinical department of Akademiska hospital in 1939, a district physician in Gothenburg from 1940-1941, and a chief physician at Vasa hospital in Gothenburg since 1941. Has written about 30 scientific papers on internal medicine and neurological disorders.
